Another bestseller for Hillary Clinton. Her political novel, “State of Terror” is flying off bookstore shelves. Not to be outdone by his better(?) half, former President Bill Clinton is working on his suspense novel, “Internal Affairs,” loosely based on a true story. Reader Stan Swalla with a story about two other senior citizens. “Two ladies, Dolly and Ruby, were talking about their grandkids.” Dolly said each year; “I send them a card with a check. Never hear from them. Never a thank you. Ruby replied I send my grandkids a check and hear from them in a week. In fact, they pay me a visit. Dolly: Really? Ruby: Simple. I don’t sign the check.” Starry, starry night in L.A. The National League hasn’t won the All-Star Game since 2012. That doesn’t matter.  The Rays’ Shane McClanahan will start for the American League, the Dodgers’ Clayton Kershaw for the NL. That doesn’t matter. A gallon of gas is over $6 in California. That doesn’t matter. What matters is who Stitches is betting. Play the National League.